1
00:01:31,150 --> 00:01:35,930
[Life Is a Choice]

2
00:01:38,039 --> 00:01:40,240
[Episode 5]

3
00:01:40,979 --> 00:01:42,940
[Give Myself a Green Hat]

4
00:01:43,220 --> 00:01:44,110
It feels so good

5
00:01:44,110 --> 00:01:45,870
to spend other people's money on yourself.

6
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:50,710
Jiang?

7
00:01:51,370 --> 00:01:52,170
What are you doing here?

8
00:01:52,860 --> 00:01:53,670
Waiting for you.

9
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:54,740
Come on, let's go upstairs.

10
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:57,470
Haven't you had dinner yet?

11
00:01:58,539 --> 00:01:59,630
You bought so many things.

12
00:01:59,630 --> 00:02:00,510
I bought a lot of things.

13
00:02:11,550 --> 00:02:12,710
I'm not in the mood right now

14
00:02:12,710 --> 00:02:14,310
to talk about Feng Huanan's life trajectory with you.

15
00:02:14,310 --> 00:02:16,060
I wish I could tear him apart alive.

16
00:02:17,190 --> 00:02:18,310
But sometimes

17
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:20,140
I still find him quite charming.

18
00:02:21,790 --> 00:02:23,190
I really want to give myself a good slap.

19
00:02:24,850 --> 00:02:26,670
I had some doubts before,

20
00:02:26,790 --> 00:02:28,180
but after hearing you say this,

21
00:02:28,270 --> 00:02:29,590
I'm even more certain

22
00:02:30,310 --> 00:02:31,710
that you are the real Gu Nian, no doubt.

23
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:32,940
What do you mean?

24
00:02:33,329 --> 00:02:34,490
I better not say more.

25
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,200
I might get punched.

26
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:36,390
Just say it.

27
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:37,960
Let's talk about me.

28
00:02:38,579 --> 00:02:41,260
Will I really become as awesome as you say in the future?

29
00:02:42,260 --> 00:02:44,020
Everything I told Gu Nian was true.

30
00:02:44,170 --> 00:02:46,050
A business elite, golden bachelor.

31
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:50,660
So looks like I've succeeded in my startup.

32
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,360
Jiang.

33
00:02:54,990 --> 00:02:56,270
I know what you're thinking.

34
00:02:56,450 --> 00:02:58,090
You're not allowed to start a business with Feng Huanan.

35
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,210
But if I don't start a business,

36
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,660
won't you look down on me even more?

37
00:03:01,690 --> 00:03:03,240
Well, actually...

38
00:03:03,270 --> 00:03:04,550
You're a gem.

39
00:03:04,790 --> 00:03:05,910
You'll shine wherever you go.

40
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:07,470
Moreover, in the end,

41
00:03:07,510 --> 00:03:09,100
you still parted ways with Feng Huanan

42
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:09,940
and went off to start your own business.

43
00:03:10,910 --> 00:03:12,190
Isn't that the same if you start on your own

44
00:03:12,190 --> 00:03:12,910
from the beginning?

45
00:03:13,710 --> 00:03:15,190
Don't worry, am I the kind of person

46
00:03:15,190 --> 00:03:16,930
who would do anything to achieve my goals?

47
00:03:16,970 --> 00:03:17,790
Besides,

48
00:03:17,790 --> 00:03:19,900
Feng Huanan and I don't graduate in the same year.

49
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:20,900
When the time comes, I'll just find an excuse

50
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:21,740
and turn him down.

51
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,240
Don't forget.

52
00:03:24,630 --> 00:03:26,040
You still need to keep pursuing Gu Nian.

53
00:03:28,220 --> 00:03:29,020
Boss,

54
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:31,270
when it comes to matters of the heart,

55
00:03:31,270 --> 00:03:33,710
they can't be one-sided.

56
00:03:34,030 --> 00:03:35,150
It's obvious

57
00:03:35,270 --> 00:03:37,340
that neither the current you nor the future you

58
00:03:37,340 --> 00:03:39,510
is very interested in me.

59
00:03:39,950 --> 00:03:42,390
I still want to focus my limited energy

60
00:03:42,650 --> 00:03:44,250
on personal improvement.

61
00:03:51,730 --> 00:03:52,650
Let me try to find some feelings.

62
00:04:03,530 --> 00:04:04,640
Still can't find any.

63
00:04:06,510 --> 00:04:06,950
Gu Nian.

64
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:09,590
How many days has it been since you last showered?

65
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,360
Su Yin stinks.

66
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,740
I don't have time to take a shower.

67
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,350
Go take a shower.

68
00:04:18,790 --> 00:04:20,260
The smell is coming in waves.

69
00:04:21,170 --> 00:04:21,850
I...

70
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:24,880
go to the men's bathhouse to shower?

71
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,440
I'll go in and take a look first.

72
00:04:43,970 --> 00:04:45,050
You stay here and wait for me.

73
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:45,510
Okay.

74
00:05:12,620 --> 00:05:13,270
Boss.

75
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:14,980
Shower in the next round.

76
00:05:15,060 --> 00:05:15,980
It's packed in there.

77
00:05:16,010 --> 00:05:17,480
You scrub for ages and don't even know who you're scrubbing.

78
00:05:18,820 --> 00:05:20,520
Boss, where are you going?

79
00:05:21,130 --> 00:05:22,010
Jiang, you don't understand.

80
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,430
As a married woman with a child

81
00:05:23,430 --> 00:05:24,510
who wasted seven years of her life,

82
00:05:24,510 --> 00:05:25,780
I've never seen a sight like this before!

83
00:05:25,960 --> 00:05:27,600
To think of all the great guys I missed out on back then!

84
00:05:27,750 --> 00:05:29,230
What kind of spell did Feng Huanan cast on me?

85
00:05:29,690 --> 00:05:30,450
Come back here.

86
00:05:31,420 --> 00:05:32,820
Can't you have some self-respect?

87
00:05:32,820 --> 00:05:33,870
You're in a man's body now.

88
00:05:33,870 --> 00:05:35,590
When you go in, don't stare at those men.

89
00:05:35,590 --> 00:05:36,510
You'll easily get beaten up!

90
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,190
What if you get exposed?

91
00:05:40,159 --> 00:05:40,960
Go then.

92
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,530
Jiang, come with me.

93
00:05:46,670 --> 00:05:47,390
Let's see if I can find some feelings in there.

94
00:05:48,140 --> 00:05:48,940
Boss.

95
00:05:49,470 --> 00:05:51,470
If we keep looking for feelings, we won't have any left.

96
00:05:52,350 --> 00:05:53,070
Rest assured.

97
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:54,220
I definitely won't agree to

98
00:05:54,250 --> 00:05:55,330
starting a business with Feng Huanan.

99
00:06:20,990 --> 00:06:21,480
I'm off.

100
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:22,270
Take care.

101
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:27,750
Sis,

102
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:30,510
can I use your bathroom to take a shower?

103
00:06:35,790 --> 00:06:37,070
-No.
-It's not what you think.

104
00:06:37,070 --> 00:06:38,150
You guys...

105
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:40,440
Su Yin, you're quite impressive.

106
00:06:40,470 --> 00:06:41,470
Couldn't get me,

107
00:06:41,590 --> 00:06:43,020
so you've moved on to Lin Xi, huh?

108
00:06:43,110 --> 00:06:45,390
A complete makeover from head to toe, huh?

109
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,390
Is it similar?

110
00:06:50,770 --> 00:06:51,530
Similar to what?

111
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:53,420
The colors you like

112
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,560
and combinations of clothes you like.

113
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:55,560
How is it?

114
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:58,070
Su Yin, I used to think

115
00:06:58,159 --> 00:06:59,680
you were just unreliable,

116
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:01,220
but it turns out you're secretly flirtatious.

117
00:07:01,510 --> 00:07:02,190
Lin Xi,

118
00:07:02,210 --> 00:07:03,690
since when did you start liking this type?

119
00:07:03,850 --> 00:07:05,120
No, you've really misunderstood.

120
00:07:05,220 --> 00:07:06,110
I don't like him.

121
00:07:06,110 --> 00:07:06,870
He doesn't like me either.

122
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:07,980
There's nothing, nothing going on between us.

123
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:09,460
Why are you in such a hurry to explain?

124
00:07:10,140 --> 00:07:12,470
You two have only known each other for a couple of days, right?

125
00:07:12,470 --> 00:07:13,190
Love at first sight, huh?

126
00:07:13,190 --> 00:07:15,110
-Where did that come from?
-Where did that come from?

127
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:16,470
Mutual affection?

128
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:18,300
It's not a mutual affection. There's nothing between us!

129
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:19,990
You two are the same age, huh?

130
00:07:20,870 --> 00:07:21,910
Not bad, quite suitable.

131
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,280
Xi, not bad, go for it.

132
00:07:24,310 --> 00:07:25,750
What's not bad? Go for what?

133
00:07:26,590 --> 00:07:27,520
No, Nian!

134
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:28,350
You, you've got it wrong...

135
00:07:28,350 --> 00:07:29,110
Xi!

136
00:07:29,110 --> 00:07:29,750
What?

137
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:30,780
Why bother explaining to her?

138
00:07:30,810 --> 00:07:31,690
The mere sight of her irritates me.

139
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:33,000
Why not explain it?

140
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:34,510
Lin Xi, go for it.

141
00:07:38,150 --> 00:07:39,050
Me, go for it?

142
00:07:39,390 --> 00:07:41,030
No, what are you... Nian!

143
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:43,710
She doesn't have a single brain cell.

144
00:07:43,790 --> 00:07:44,590
She asked me to find evidence.

145
00:07:44,590 --> 00:07:46,030
Isn't this, isn't this obvious enough?

146
00:07:46,150 --> 00:07:47,270
You've got a good brain, huh?

147
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:49,250
You just now, like this...

148
00:07:50,170 --> 00:07:51,120
Unbelievable.

149
00:07:52,590 --> 00:07:53,580
She now thinks you...

150
00:07:54,870 --> 00:07:55,350
Forget it.

151
00:07:55,370 --> 00:07:56,150
You two are exactly the same

152
00:07:56,150 --> 00:07:56,760
when you're out of your mind.

153
00:07:57,909 --> 00:07:58,909
Why did she come to you?

154
00:07:59,550 --> 00:07:59,990
About that.

155
00:08:01,660 --> 00:08:02,990
She might as well ask me to check

156
00:08:02,990 --> 00:08:04,330
if I'm a normal person or not.

157
00:08:07,230 --> 00:08:09,220
[Certificate of Honor; Mr. Su Yin: Named an Outstanding Communist Youth League Cadre of 2017]

158
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:14,420
You've won quite a few awards.

159
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:14,520
[VR Game]

160
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:14,520
[Certificate of Honor]

161
00:08:15,780 --> 00:08:16,510
It's Su Yin.

162
00:08:18,420 --> 00:08:18,990
Right.

163
00:08:20,370 --> 00:08:21,610
You don't have the brains for these.

164
00:08:23,620 --> 00:08:25,390
[Heyuan University Facial Identification System]

165
00:08:23,620 --> 00:08:25,390
[Quality Management System Certification]

166
00:08:29,510 --> 00:08:31,580
[In the Huaidong Province University Computer Design Competition, Su Yin was awarded first place]

167
00:08:45,340 --> 00:08:46,120
Just these.

168
00:08:47,070 --> 00:08:48,230
It's so obvious.

169
00:08:48,270 --> 00:08:49,470
These are enough to prove

170
00:08:49,490 --> 00:08:50,180
that Su Yin and I,

171
00:08:50,180 --> 00:08:51,910
aside from that one time I took him when his grandfather was sick,

172
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:53,350
have had no other interactions.

173
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,400
Besides, he's not even from this city.

174
00:08:56,420 --> 00:08:57,340
He grew up with his grandfather.

175
00:08:57,750 --> 00:08:58,550
So why would I

176
00:08:58,550 --> 00:09:00,110
travel back in time and inhabit his body?

177
00:09:00,110 --> 00:09:00,950
That doesn't make any sense at all.

178
00:09:03,230 --> 00:09:05,310
Nian, I'm a doctor,

179
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:06,670
not a psychic.

180
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,200
I don't know it either.

181
00:09:09,050 --> 00:09:10,390
Then why do you believe him?

182
00:09:10,710 --> 00:09:12,230
Just because he told you some

183
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:14,140
rather private details?

184
00:09:15,060 --> 00:09:16,870
His behavior, mannerisms,

185
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:18,650
and thought processes are all very similar to yours.

186
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:19,750
How are they similar?

187
00:09:20,310 --> 00:09:21,510
He's just a lunatic.

188
00:09:22,230 --> 00:09:23,190
And because of him,

189
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,900
starting tomorrow, I have to play a tree.

190
00:09:24,970 --> 00:09:26,090
Can you believe it?

191
00:09:27,870 --> 00:09:28,310
Then,

192
00:09:29,010 --> 00:09:30,450
let's just stick to the most objective facts.

193
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,560
He, his speech is quite clear, isn't it?

194
00:09:32,830 --> 00:09:34,300
His thinking is quite sharp, right?

195
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,990
Even the psychiatric department couldn't find

196
00:09:35,990 --> 00:09:36,910
any problems with him.

197
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:37,630
That's pretty scientific.

198
00:09:37,790 --> 00:09:39,270
That's the biggest problem.

199
00:09:39,420 --> 00:09:40,450
I've looked it up online.

200
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:41,870
All these stories about time travel to fix regrets,

201
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:42,780
they all say

202
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:43,950
it'd only happen as a dying person

203
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:45,710
enters the body of another dying person.

204
00:09:45,940 --> 00:09:47,030
I've checked it all out.

205
00:09:47,110 --> 00:09:49,270
He's been in perfect health since he entered university.

206
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:51,470
So if the future me is in his body,

207
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:52,300
what about his own self?

208
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:58,350
Well, you have a point there.

209
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:02,390
Lin Xi.

210
00:10:02,970 --> 00:10:04,480
Does your hospital have a lie detector?

211
00:10:05,450 --> 00:10:06,880
You've been watching too many TV dramas.

212
00:10:08,050 --> 00:10:08,760
So,

213
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:09,620
I think you

214
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:10,580
should get your head checked.

215
00:10:10,850 --> 00:10:12,010
Otherwise, how could you believe him?

216
00:10:14,230 --> 00:10:17,230
Both of your handwriting is identical.

217
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:21,400
Look.

218
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:26,090
Why don't you write something?

219
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:26,960
See for yourself.

220
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:28,690
No way.

221
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,470
No, I need to have this professionally examined.

222
00:10:31,820 --> 00:10:33,230
How can they be exactly the same?

223
00:10:33,250 --> 00:10:34,720
This is impossible.

224
00:10:36,170 --> 00:10:36,980
Xi.

225
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:39,690
I'm really conflicted.

226
00:10:41,490 --> 00:10:42,810
Don't be too ridiculous.

227
00:10:43,370 --> 00:10:44,900
Can't you be more conflicted than I am?

228
00:10:45,410 --> 00:10:47,370
I'm grateful that I wasn't that stupid before,

229
00:10:48,450 --> 00:10:50,210
but it's precisely because I wasn't that stupid

230
00:10:50,910 --> 00:10:52,720
that I'm really at a loss now.

231
00:10:54,210 --> 00:10:55,810
Now you think you're not stupid.

232
00:10:56,010 --> 00:10:56,850
Then what?

233
00:10:56,850 --> 00:10:58,010
You're dragging me into the middle of all this.

234
00:10:58,010 --> 00:10:59,290
Who am I supposed to talk to about this?

235
00:11:02,210 --> 00:11:03,010
Nian,

236
00:11:03,820 --> 00:11:05,320
I don't know what you've been through

237
00:11:05,610 --> 00:11:07,010
all these years

238
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:08,780
to become the way you are now,

239
00:11:09,410 --> 00:11:11,300
but you've really changed a lot

240
00:11:11,610 --> 00:11:12,770
from the person I used to know.

241
00:11:13,290 --> 00:11:13,840
Xi,

242
00:11:14,570 --> 00:11:15,960
which one do you think is more clear-headed,

243
00:11:16,710 --> 00:11:18,420
the past me or the current me?

244
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:20,850
You should ask,

245
00:11:21,570 --> 00:11:22,890
"Which one is more carefree?"

246
00:11:24,970 --> 00:11:27,010
Am I really that incapable of letting go?

247
00:11:27,210 --> 00:11:28,290
You've seen it yourself.

248
00:11:28,650 --> 00:11:31,210
Your past self would sometimes act like a little girl,

249
00:11:31,980 --> 00:11:33,490
experiencing countless emotions in a single day.

250
00:11:34,210 --> 00:11:36,800
But you could quickly heal and recover on your own.

251
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:38,940
Open and genuine.

252
00:11:39,810 --> 00:11:41,290
When you liked something, you weren't afraid to show it.

253
00:11:41,370 --> 00:11:42,530
When you disliked something, you made it clear.

254
00:11:49,570 --> 00:11:50,610
You're right.

255
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:52,690
But I really don't know what to do anymore.

256
00:11:53,410 --> 00:11:54,410
You've seen it yourself.

257
00:11:54,730 --> 00:11:56,700
She doesn't believe it when I show up with the same dressing style and preferences.

258
00:11:57,210 --> 00:11:58,650
She doesn't believe it either when you show her the same handwriting.

259
00:11:59,770 --> 00:12:01,720
My future memories stop at the hospital.

260
00:12:02,410 --> 00:12:03,650
They stripped everything

261
00:12:03,930 --> 00:12:05,450
off me in the emergency room.

262
00:12:06,290 --> 00:12:08,250
You should know yourself better than I do.

263
00:12:10,130 --> 00:12:14,090
Why don't you try to put yourself in your past self's shoes?

264
00:12:15,690 --> 00:12:18,970
You mean... seeing is believing?

265
00:12:21,610 --> 00:12:22,530
But I don't know

266
00:12:22,530 --> 00:12:24,050
when Feng Huanan started

267
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:25,090
turning into such a scumbag.

268
00:12:31,490 --> 00:12:32,130
Nian.

269
00:12:33,610 --> 00:12:34,810
Do you remember what happened with my father?

270
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,370
Xi, don't think about it.

271
00:12:36,370 --> 00:12:37,010
I didn't mean it that way.

272
00:12:37,010 --> 00:12:38,010
No, this is important.

273
00:12:40,810 --> 00:12:42,210
Actually, I want to figure out

274
00:12:42,970 --> 00:12:44,410
what exactly happened.

275
00:12:45,010 --> 00:12:45,730
Trust me.

276
00:12:46,890 --> 00:12:47,970
When you discover that a man

277
00:12:47,970 --> 00:12:49,200
has already cheated,

278
00:12:49,490 --> 00:12:51,410
it's definitely not something that just happened.

279
00:12:54,580 --> 00:12:55,810
Every time it was brought up...

280
00:12:58,010 --> 00:12:59,210
I feel so sad.

281
00:13:05,650 --> 00:13:07,010
I think I should take a shower

282
00:13:08,530 --> 00:13:10,130
to wash away all the bad luck on me.

283
00:13:11,210 --> 00:13:11,810
Right?

284
00:13:12,010 --> 00:13:12,450
What?

285
00:13:12,450 --> 00:13:12,890
Yes.

286
00:13:13,170 --> 00:13:14,250
I'm going to take a shower then, Xi.

287
00:13:15,870 --> 00:13:17,250
No, Gu Nian, don't go too far!

288
00:13:18,250 --> 00:13:19,260
Don't use my towel!

289
00:13:19,260 --> 00:13:20,260
You're a man now!

290
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:38,610
You go ahead. I'll handle it.

291
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:41,830
President.

292
00:13:42,290 --> 00:13:43,660
Everything you asked for is ready.

293
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:44,150
Alright.

294
00:13:44,380 --> 00:13:45,900
President, let's go get something to eat.

295
00:13:46,050 --> 00:13:46,810
I haven't had breakfast yet.

296
00:13:46,810 --> 00:13:47,690
I'll keep setting up.

297
00:13:47,690 --> 00:13:48,490
You guys go ahead.

298
00:13:48,490 --> 00:13:49,420
Don't worry about me.

299
00:13:49,570 --> 00:13:50,370
Let's go together.

300
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:51,940
You go first. I'm not hungry.

301
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,570
Then, how about we bring you some soup dumplings?

302
00:13:53,610 --> 00:13:54,260
Okay.

303
00:13:54,770 --> 00:13:55,330
Alright.

304
00:13:55,450 --> 00:13:56,250
We're off then.

305
00:13:56,250 --> 00:13:57,490
Okay, don't eat too much.

306
00:13:57,490 --> 00:13:58,170
We have a rehearsal later.

307
00:13:58,170 --> 00:13:58,850
Got it.

308
00:13:59,250 --> 00:13:59,810
We're off.

309
00:14:18,690 --> 00:14:19,810
Wh-when did you get here?

310
00:14:19,810 --> 00:14:20,740
You walk so quietly.

311
00:14:20,810 --> 00:14:21,610
Here, catch it.

312
00:14:23,450 --> 00:14:25,400
You've done an amazing job with this.

313
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:27,650
Let me show you.

314
00:14:28,690 --> 00:14:29,410
Watch this.

315
00:14:32,890 --> 00:14:34,220
Here we go.

316
00:14:40,370 --> 00:14:42,130
How did you come up with the idea of using fishing line?

317
00:14:42,450 --> 00:14:43,780
When I was little, my mom, for some reason,

318
00:14:43,930 --> 00:14:44,980
really wanted to use my dad's

319
00:14:45,170 --> 00:14:46,490
old fishing line to string chili peppers.

320
00:14:47,010 --> 00:14:47,490
And then,

321
00:14:47,490 --> 00:14:49,250
after stringing them, she would, like this,

322
00:14:49,450 --> 00:14:51,580
hang them out in the wind like this.

323
00:14:51,650 --> 00:14:52,650
And at that time, I,

324
00:14:52,770 --> 00:14:55,410
I'd stand underneath with my eyes closed,

325
00:14:55,410 --> 00:14:56,770
spinning around and around.

326
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:57,650
I would just keep spinning.

327
00:14:57,650 --> 00:14:58,530
Then I'd open my eyes.

328
00:14:59,370 --> 00:15:00,770
When I opened them, I'd find

329
00:15:00,770 --> 00:15:02,770
it looked like there were real clouds,

330
00:15:03,090 --> 00:15:04,690
white clouds floating in the sky.

331
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:05,900
It was so magical.

332
00:15:07,050 --> 00:15:09,610
After hearing you say that, I could even smell

333
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:11,650
the aroma of

334
00:15:11,650 --> 00:15:13,880
chili pepper skins filling the air.

335
00:15:14,090 --> 00:15:15,770
And in my mind, I can see

336
00:15:16,090 --> 00:15:17,280
Grandma using a bamboo sieve

337
00:15:17,380 --> 00:15:20,230
to separate the dried peppers and seeds.

338
00:15:21,010 --> 00:15:24,560
Then she'd heat up oil by the stove

339
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:25,910
and add

340
00:15:26,530 --> 00:15:29,330
Sichuan peppercorns, star anise,

341
00:15:29,330 --> 00:15:30,690
cinnamon, and sesame seeds,

342
00:15:30,860 --> 00:15:33,290
roasting the chili seeds until they became crispy and fragrant

343
00:15:33,310 --> 00:15:35,700
and pouring them all into a jar to make spicy five-spice seasoning!

344
00:15:36,370 --> 00:15:37,090
Are you homesick?

345
00:15:37,630 --> 00:15:38,840
No.

346
00:15:39,610 --> 00:15:40,570
If I told you

347
00:15:40,570 --> 00:15:42,390
I've never been homesick, would you believe me?

348
00:15:42,730 --> 00:15:44,980
Sure, why wouldn't I?

349
00:15:45,890 --> 00:15:47,120
Not everyone's home

350
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,450
is warm and sweet.

351
00:15:49,530 --> 00:15:51,580
If you don't miss home, it's a problem with your home,

352
00:15:52,290 --> 00:15:53,420
not with you.

353
00:15:54,430 --> 00:15:55,450
Oh, let me tell you,

354
00:15:55,690 --> 00:15:57,170
when I first got to university,

355
00:15:57,290 --> 00:15:58,330
during the first week,

356
00:15:58,570 --> 00:16:00,020
all my dormmates cried

357
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:01,530
because they were homesick.

358
00:16:01,570 --> 00:16:02,340
I was the only one who didn't cry.

359
00:16:02,690 --> 00:16:05,090
I felt really happy and excited at the time.

360
00:16:05,570 --> 00:16:08,450
Because I felt like I was finally free.
-Free!

361
00:16:10,610 --> 00:16:11,250
Right?

362
00:16:14,170 --> 00:16:14,810
Let me tell you something:

363
00:16:14,810 --> 00:16:17,050
I never went back home after the college entrance exam.

364
00:16:17,770 --> 00:16:18,490
Because I felt

365
00:16:18,490 --> 00:16:20,090
that I hadn't amounted to much academically.

366
00:16:20,110 --> 00:16:21,480
I was too embarrassed to go back.

367
00:16:21,770 --> 00:16:23,090
It would be so humiliating to return.

368
00:16:23,570 --> 00:16:26,220
Me too. I don't like going back home either.

369
00:16:26,810 --> 00:16:29,570
But sometimes

370
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:31,340
I still need to go back to see my father.

371
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:34,020
Didn't you ask me before

372
00:16:34,370 --> 00:16:36,040
why I'm still sticking with the drama club

373
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:37,450
when I'm about to graduate?

374
00:16:39,170 --> 00:16:40,490
Because the left-behind children

375
00:16:40,490 --> 00:16:42,210
our charity performances support

376
00:16:42,870 --> 00:16:44,070
are just like us.

377
00:16:45,490 --> 00:16:45,930
The CCYL Committee

378
00:16:45,930 --> 00:16:48,130
needs to evaluate their situation for three consecutive years

379
00:16:48,410 --> 00:16:50,410
before they can be placed on

380
00:16:50,610 --> 00:16:51,930
the long-term support list.

381
00:16:53,180 --> 00:16:54,250
By the time I found out about this,

382
00:16:54,250 --> 00:16:55,290
I was already in my sophomore year.

383
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:59,280
Yes, I could've graduated and stopped caring about them,

384
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:01,930
but what would happen to them?

385
00:17:04,250 --> 00:17:05,170
I didn't expect

386
00:17:05,450 --> 00:17:07,700
that you'd still harbor such a noble ideal.

387
00:17:10,290 --> 00:17:12,210
I don't have any noble ideals.

388
00:17:12,609 --> 00:17:13,849
I just sometimes wonder

389
00:17:13,849 --> 00:17:15,290
if someone had done all this

390
00:17:15,690 --> 00:17:17,819
for me from afar

391
00:17:18,089 --> 00:17:18,970
when I was a child,

392
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:21,010
maybe my future

393
00:17:21,010 --> 00:17:22,290
would have turned out differently.

394
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:25,619
You make a good point,

395
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:28,210
though if that had happened,

396
00:17:28,210 --> 00:17:29,890
we might never have met.

397
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:35,490
Yeah, when you put it that way,

398
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:37,050
it does seem like a bit of a shame.

399
00:17:39,740 --> 00:17:40,320
Oh, right!

400
00:17:41,330 --> 00:17:42,840
When you were picking chili peppers there,

401
00:17:43,130 --> 00:17:44,220
did the girls dance?

402
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:46,090
I think they did, yeah.

403
00:17:46,930 --> 00:17:49,010
The dance they did at that time was called...

404
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:51,000
I'll dance it for you.

405
00:17:51,450 --> 00:17:52,580
Is this how it went?

406
00:18:39,460 --> 00:18:40,900
Not bad.

407
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:43,210
No, I just learned it.

408
00:18:43,210 --> 00:18:44,010
I'm not dancing well.

409
00:18:44,010 --> 00:18:45,010
Why are you here?

410
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:45,850
What are you doing?

411
00:18:46,370 --> 00:18:47,650
What are you doing? You, you, you...

412
00:18:47,650 --> 00:18:48,610
Put that down! Put that down!

413
00:18:52,230 --> 00:18:52,840
Reimburse.

414
00:18:54,090 --> 00:18:55,610
Reimburse? Reimburse what?

415
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:17,770
This can't be reimbursed right now.

416
00:19:19,090 --> 00:19:21,250
Why? The teacher said you have all the money.

417
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:23,810
This money was for our charity performance

418
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:26,780
for children in the mountain areas of Guizhou.

419
00:19:26,780 --> 00:19:28,250
I need to transfer it this afternoon.

420
00:19:30,930 --> 00:19:31,450
This weekend.

421
00:19:31,850 --> 00:19:34,090
Isn't there a performance at the nursing home this weekend?

422
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,380
I think there will be some money.

423
00:19:35,690 --> 00:19:36,610
I'll give it to you then,

424
00:19:36,850 --> 00:19:37,360
okay?

425
00:19:38,130 --> 00:19:38,770
Bro.

426
00:19:39,890 --> 00:19:40,450
Okay?

427
00:19:44,090 --> 00:19:44,770
Fine.

428
00:19:45,610 --> 00:19:46,650
I'm not in a hurry to use the money anyway.

429
00:19:50,250 --> 00:19:50,930
You dance pretty well.

430
00:19:51,450 --> 00:19:52,170
Keep dancing.

431
00:19:59,210 --> 00:19:59,850
Gu Nian?

432
00:20:02,910 --> 00:20:03,890
Let go of me first.

433
00:20:04,410 --> 00:20:05,410
Why are you running?

434
00:20:05,410 --> 00:20:06,380
I'm not a ghost.

435
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:10,210
Is it fun for you to wear the same clothes as me every day?

436
00:20:10,430 --> 00:20:11,270
It's so annoying.

437
00:20:12,730 --> 00:20:14,250
Can't help it. We're the same soul.

438
00:20:15,030 --> 00:20:17,160
Oh, let me show you something interesting.

439
00:20:26,630 --> 00:20:27,790
What's going on?

440
00:20:28,210 --> 00:20:29,970
They're even dancing together now.

441
00:20:30,780 --> 00:20:32,220
This pair of scumbags.

442
00:20:32,620 --> 00:20:33,410
Scumbags.

443
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:34,890
What are you talking about?

444
00:20:34,910 --> 00:20:36,150
Not manly at all.

445
00:20:38,510 --> 00:20:40,780
Gu Nian, I think we're both so stupid.

446
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:41,940
We didn't even know

447
00:20:42,430 --> 00:20:44,120
when they started hooking up.

448
00:20:45,930 --> 00:20:47,780
Does dancing together mean they're a couple?

449
00:20:47,810 --> 00:20:49,930
Then you ran to Lin Xi's house to take a shower late at nightâ€”

450
00:20:49,930 --> 00:20:51,210
does that mean you're living together unmarried?

451
00:20:52,610 --> 00:20:53,450
You're such an idiot.

452
00:20:53,490 --> 00:20:54,650
Just go ahead and be stupid.

453
00:20:56,090 --> 00:20:57,370
How could I have been so stupid back then?

454
00:21:07,010 --> 00:21:08,170
What is this?

455
00:21:08,410 --> 00:21:09,930
I made it myself, for you.

456
00:21:10,210 --> 00:21:12,050
Once you've been cheated on, you won't love anyone.

457
00:21:12,670 --> 00:21:13,780
Are you crazy or something?

458
00:21:15,130 --> 00:21:16,010
You're the one who's crazy.

459
00:21:16,430 --> 00:21:17,430
What kind of man are you?

460
00:21:19,660 --> 00:21:20,890
I can't do it, really can't do it.

461
00:21:21,540 --> 00:21:22,190
Nian?

462
00:21:23,050 --> 00:21:24,090
What are you two doing?

463
00:21:25,410 --> 00:21:26,820
Gu Nian, we're going to the cafeteria.

464
00:21:26,820 --> 00:21:27,490
Why don't you join us?

465
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:28,580
Well...

466
00:21:28,740 --> 00:21:29,570
I'm not hungry.

467
00:21:29,570 --> 00:21:30,170
She's not hungry.

468
00:21:31,660 --> 00:21:32,810
Alright, if you're not going.

469
00:21:33,210 --> 00:21:34,490
I'll leave this key with you.

470
00:21:34,810 --> 00:21:35,570
Before we come back,

471
00:21:35,570 --> 00:21:36,570
make sure someone's here.

472
00:21:36,710 --> 00:21:39,030
If anything goes missing, it's on us.

473
00:21:42,110 --> 00:21:42,710
Let's go.

474
00:21:43,050 --> 00:21:43,570
Let's go.

475
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:44,560
Bye-bye.

476
00:21:44,590 --> 00:21:45,250
Eat more, okay?

477
00:21:49,410 --> 00:21:51,210
We'll just do our own thing.

478
00:21:51,210 --> 00:21:51,970
No interference with each other.

479
00:21:52,140 --> 00:21:53,990
As if I like being around you.

480
00:21:54,820 --> 00:21:55,500
Wait a moment!

481
00:21:57,050 --> 00:21:57,690
Take it back!

482
00:22:01,150 --> 00:22:02,060
It suits you better.

483
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:03,360
You...

484
00:22:24,270 --> 00:22:27,580
[First Cafeteria]

485
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:45,330
I'd like to see

486
00:22:45,330 --> 00:22:47,070
where you've spent all the money.

487
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,240
This can't be reimbursed for now.

488
00:23:32,710 --> 00:23:34,870
Why? The teacher said you have all the money.

489
00:23:34,980 --> 00:23:37,260
This money was for our charity performance

490
00:23:38,010 --> 00:23:40,410
for children in the mountain areas of Guizhou.

491
00:23:40,410 --> 00:23:41,820
I need to transfer it this afternoon.

492
00:24:09,170 --> 00:24:10,130
Your dumplings are here.

493
00:24:10,450 --> 00:24:11,170
Okay, thank you.

494
00:24:11,260 --> 00:24:12,710
Would you like to order anything else?

495
00:24:13,210 --> 00:24:13,930
What do you have?

496
00:24:14,690 --> 00:24:15,610
We're out of tofu pudding.

497
00:24:15,610 --> 00:24:17,250
We only have wontons, soy milk, and porridge left.

498
00:24:17,250 --> 00:24:18,170
What would you like?

499
00:24:20,490 --> 00:24:21,130
Are you hungry?

500
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:24,970
Mommy bought wontons, porridge, and dumplings.

501
00:24:25,150 --> 00:24:26,190
Which one would you like to eat?

502
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,900
We haven't had any fruit today.

503
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:31,040
How about eating a small apple?

504
00:24:31,180 --> 00:24:33,990
Mommy, I don't like eating fruit.

505
00:24:35,090 --> 00:24:37,290
Mommy can cut the small apple

506
00:24:37,290 --> 00:24:38,610
into a little star.

507
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:42,010
Then, maybe I'll consider it.

508
00:24:43,170 --> 00:24:44,330
What would you like to order?

509
00:24:46,750 --> 00:24:48,830
Sir, is there any place nearby that sells apples?

510
00:24:49,510 --> 00:24:51,220
There's a fruit shop if you turn left up ahead.

511
00:24:52,990 --> 00:24:54,910
Alright, then please pack these for me.

512
00:24:54,940 --> 00:24:55,270
Okay.

513
00:24:55,300 --> 00:24:55,790
Thank you.

514
00:24:56,110 --> 00:24:56,780
Just a moment, please.

515
00:25:29,460 --> 00:25:32,240
Mommy, I miss Daddy.

516
00:25:32,410 --> 00:25:34,290
Today is my birthday.

517
00:25:34,290 --> 00:25:36,810
